/*

PSUEDOCODE

game initials a board of 4x4 (16) facedown cards.

player is prompted to click cards and make matches.

as soon as player clicks a card a timer begins as the card is "flipped" or revealed, counting up to see how much time the player takes to finish a game.

with each additional card click and reveal, a counter increases by one, indicated how many total moves the player has made.

for every 2 cards revealed, the cards are checked to be matching, and if so, are left revealed.  if not matching, are turned back over.

once all cards are revealed and matched, the timer stops and the a message states how many moves and in how much time the player took for the game.

reset button at bottom of the screen to play again.









*/